# elizaos/elizaos.github.io Daily Update (Jan 23, 2026)
## OVERVIEW 
Today's development focused on addressing inconsistencies in repository data display. A new pull request was opened to consolidate the untracked repositories pipeline, and a new issue was raised regarding the differing column counts between tracked and untracked repository tables.

## KEY TECHNICAL DEVELOPMENTS

## NEWLY OPENED PULL REQUESTS
- **Pipeline Consolidation and DRY Fixes:** A new pull request, [#231](https://github.com/elizaos/elizaos.github.io/pull/231), was opened to consolidate the untracked repositories pipeline and address DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself) violations.

## CLOSED ISSUES

## NEW ISSUES
- **Untracked Repositories Table Discrepancy:** A new issue, [#230](https://github.com/elizaos/elizaos.github.io/issues/230), was created to highlight that the untracked repositories table currently displays twice as many columns as the tracked repositories table.
